Hi Elizabeth,

To be honest, I don't understand your teacher's explanation.  There
are, in fact, 32 ways to choose combinations of 5 items.  To see why,
look at 

  Fast food combinations.
  http://mathforum.org/dr.math/faq/faq.mcdonalds.html

and write back if it's not clear, or if you still have questions. 

Does this help?

